creator: Gallus Golf
descriptionHtml:
Download the Lakeside Golf Club -Alberta app to enhance your golf experience!

This app includes:
- Interactive Scorecard
- Golf Games: Skins, Stableford, Par, Stroke Scoring
- GPS
- Measure your shot!
- Golfer Profile with Automatic Stats Tracker
- Hole Descriptions & Playing Tips
- Live Tournaments & Leaderboards
- Book Tee Times
- Course Tour
- Food & Beverage Menu
- Facebook Sharing
- And much more…

Welcome to Lakeside Golf Club. Located in Chestermere, Alberta the course is a mere 20 minute drive from downtown Calgary and easily accessible from other quadrants since the opening of Stoney Trail.

A well-manicured layout awaits you with large, beautiful greens, numerous tee complexes to compliment all levels of players, and many attractive water features to add to the visual appeal and challenge. Our spacious clubhouse offers our patrons a fully stocked Pro Shop featuring the latest in golf club technology, with onsite custom fitting by our PGA of Canada professionals, as well as the latest in golf attire and streetwise casual attire for both ladies and gentlemen. Stop in after golf or for a cocktail and dinner in the new Rusty Putter Grill, Lakeside’s outstanding new restaurant. Let Chef John Santos delight your taste buds with his delicious fare, and try our expanded selection of exciting local and regional craft beers on tap. Tee times are available 7 days a week for your convenience on-line through our website, or you can call the pro shop to book your times.

A limited number of Equity Memberships are now available as well at an amazing price, with package deals for the entire family. Become a member today at Southern Alberta’s Friendliest Golf Course!!

Welcome to Lakeside Golf Club. Located in Chestermere, Alberta the course is a mere 20 minute drive from downtown Calgary and easily accessible from other quadrants since the opening of Stoney Trail.

A well-manicured layout awaits you with large, beautiful greens, numerous tee complexes to compliment all levels of players, and many attractive water features to add to the visual appeal and challenge. Our spacious clubhouse offers our patrons a fully stocked Pro Shop featuring the latest in golf club technology, with onsite custom fitting by our PGA of Canada professionals, as well as the latest in golf attire and streetwise casual attire for both ladies and gentlemen. Stop in after golf or for a cocktail and dinner in the new Rusty Putter Grill, Lakeside’s outstanding new restaurant. Let Chef John Santos delight your taste buds with his delicious fare, and try our expanded selection of exciting local and regional craft beers on tap. Tee times are available 7 days a week for your convenience on-line through our website, or you can call the pro shop to book your times.
